commit a0a1043784d48c5e9be90d6f65d6b0e48ad4434f
Author: Václav Slavík <vaclav@slavik.io>
Date:   Thu Jul 14 19:40:51 2016 +0200

    Use WinInet asynchronously
    
    This is more complicated, but necessary to be able to cancel download
    operations in progress. With the (synchronous) InternetReadFile() call
    previously used, the call was all-or-nothing and couldn't be cancelled
    by the user if in progress. This would present a problem e.g. when
    suddenly loosing connectivity, in which case the call would block
    indefinitely waiting for data.
    
    Instead, use the more complicated async API and check for user-initiated
    cancellation while waiting for download data.
    
    Fixes #108.

