    Merge pull request #77 from artillery/seamless
    
    Checks if an update is available, showing progress UI to the user and
    immediately installing the update if one is available.
    
    This is useful for the case when users should almost always use the newest
    version of your software. When called, WinSparkle will check for updates
    showing a progress UI to the user. If an update is found the update prompt will
    be skipped and the update will be installed immediately.
    
    If your application expects to do something after checking for updates you may
    wish to use win_sparkle_set_did_not_find_update_callback() and
    win_sparkle_set_update_cancelled_callback().

